text: Raed al Atar (1974 - 21 August 2014) was a Palestinian military personal. He was the commander of the Rafah company of the Hamas Izz ad-Din al-Qassam Brigades. He was also a member of the Hamas high military council. According to the Congressional Research Service analyst Jim Zanotti, his command was important due to Rafah being the destination point for the smuggling tunnels from Egypt. al Atar was born in Gaza. Al Atar was killed in Rafah, Gaza on 21 August 2014 in a missiles strike by the Israeli army. ==References== Category:Rafah, Palestine Category:1974 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Asian military people Category:Hamas Category:People from the Gaza Strip Category:Palestinian Muslims Category:Palestinian nationalists Category:Palestinian militants Category:Hamas people
